    "updated_at": "2014-07-31T20:58:25Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Serving over HTTPS would not prevent malicious software running on localhost from connecting to the notebook and running code, unless you're using client certificates (which would be cumbersome as a default configuration). As far as I know, there's no real security benefit from using a secure connection on localhost. Sniffing traffic usually requires elevated privileges (at least on Linux - probably on Windows as well).\n"
  },
